---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
import TrustRulesBlock from '../components/TrustRulesBlock.astro';
import { OFFERS, OFFER_TRACKS } from '../data/offers';
import { promoLaunch } from '../data/promoLaunch';
import { withBase } from '../utils/links';

const canonicalPath = '/packages';
const trackOrder = ['launch', 'growth'] as const;
---

<MainLayout
  title="Packages | NaughtyCamSpot"
  description="The NaughtyCamSpot offer ladder from Start Right through Growth Partner, built around launch, brand, discovery, conversion, retention, and premium offers."
>
  <SEO
    slot="head"
    title="Packages | NaughtyCamSpot"
    description="The NaughtyCamSpot offer ladder from Start Right through Growth Partner, built around launch, brand, discovery, conversion, retention, and premium offers."
    path={canonicalPath}
  />

  <section class="hero-shell hero-split parallax-veil">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="eyebrow">Selected Support</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Launch support for selected models after signup basics are in place.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Most models start wrong: weak naming, no front door, random posting, random traffic, no retention structure. This ladder exists
        to fix that. These are not random promo tiers. They are the steps from cleaner setup into stronger discovery, conversion, VIP
        retention, recurring events, premium offers, and passive layers. Public focus stays on signup-first launch readiness. Selected support is reviewed case-by-case.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-sm text-parchment/64">Built for structure, not hype. Built for models who are tired of guessing.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={withBase('/apply/')}>Apply for Signup Guidance</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={withBase('/')}>Return Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-media">
      <img src="/images/home-hero-1280.jpg" alt="Editorial offer-ladder visual" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card space-y-5">
    <p class="eyebrow">What This Ladder Is</p>
    <div class="grid gap-px bg-gold/20 md:grid-cols-3">
      <p class="bg-midnight p-5 text-sm text-parchment/74">X, Instagram, TikTok, Telegram, and similar channels still matter, but they are distribution rails. They are not the business.</p>
      <p class="bg-obsidian p-5 text-sm text-parchment/74">This ladder exists because most models do not fail from lack of effort. They fail from weak structure: weak brand, weak front door, weak retention, weak repeat-spend logic.</p>
      <p class="bg-midnight p-5 text-sm text-parchment/74">These stages are not random promo tiers. They are business layers: setup, front door, identity, conversion, retention, recurring events, and stronger revenue behavior.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card space-y-5">
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <p class="eyebrow">Where You Fit</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-light text-parchment">Start with the problem you already feel.</h2>
      <p class="max-w-3xl text-sm text-parchment/70">This is not a quiz. It is a quick way to recognize the stage that is probably closest to your current bottleneck.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-px bg-gold/20 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4">
      <article class="bg-midnight p-5 text-sm text-parchment/74">
        <p class="eyebrow">Foundation / Start Right</p>
        <p>If you are new, restarting, or already feel messy before real momentum exists, this is usually where you start.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bg-obsidian p-5 text-sm text-parchment/74">
        <p class="eyebrow">Launch</p>
        <p>If people can find you but the handoff is weak, confusing, or scattered, this is usually the missing layer.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bg-midnight p-5 text-sm text-parchment/74">
        <p class="eyebrow">Brand Builder</p>
        <p>If you are active but still look generic, forgettable, or too similar to everyone else, this is usually the next step.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bg-obsidian p-5 text-sm text-parchment/74">
        <p class="eyebrow">Growth Partner</p>
        <p>If you are making money but it still feels unstable, traffic-dependent, or reset-to-reset, this is usually the right fit.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  {trackOrder.map((trackId) => {
    const track = OFFER_TRACKS[trackId];
    const offers = OFFERS.filter((offer) => offer.track === trackId);
    return (
      <section class="space-y-6">
        <div class="section-intro">
          <p class="eyebrow">{track.label}</p>
          <h2 class="section-heading">{track.description}</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid gap-6 xl:grid-cols-2">
          {offers.map((offer) => (
            <article class="content-card space-y-5">
              <div class="space-y-3">
                <p class="eyebrow">{offer.stageLabel}</p>
                <h3 class="font-display text-4xl font-light text-parchment">{offer.displayName}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-parchment/72">{offer.shortDescription}</p>
              </div>

              <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
                <div class="premium-card">
                  <p class="eyebrow">Who it is for</p>
                  <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-parchment/74">
                    {offer.forWho.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="premium-card">
                  <p class="eyebrow">Strategic deliverables</p>
                  <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-parchment/74">
                    {offer.deliverables.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
                <div class="premium-card">
                  <p class="eyebrow">NCS responsibilities</p>
                  <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-parchment/74">
                    {offer.ncsResponsibilities.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="premium-card">
                  <p class="eyebrow">Model responsibilities</p>
                  <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-parchment/74">
                    {offer.modelResponsibilities.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
                {offer.successLooksLike && (
                  <div class="premium-card">
                    <p class="eyebrow">What success looks like</p>
                    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-parchment/74">
                      {offer.successLooksLike.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                )}
                {offer.foundingModelValue && (
                  <div class="premium-card">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Founding Model Program</p>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-parchment/74"><strong class="text-parchment">Current cost:</strong> {offer.foundingModelValue.currentCost}</p>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-parchment/74"><strong class="text-parchment">Estimated value:</strong> {offer.foundingModelValue.estimatedValue}</p>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-parchment/62">{offer.foundingModelValue.note}</p>
                  </div>
                )}
                {offer.hubApproach && (
                  <div class="premium-card">
                    <p class="eyebrow">Front-door options</p>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-parchment/74"><strong class="text-parchment">Standard:</strong> {offer.hubApproach.standard}</p>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-parchment/74"><strong class="text-parchment">Premium:</strong> {offer.hubApproach.premium}</p>
                  </div>
                )}
              </div>

              {offer.upgradePath && (
                <div class="premium-card">
                  <p class="eyebrow">Why this stage exists</p>
                  <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-parchment/74">{offer.upgradePath}</p>
                </div>
              )}
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    );
  })}

  <TrustRulesBlock title="Trust rules stay fixed across the ladder" />

  <section class="content-card space-y-4">
    <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-light text-parchment">One apply flow. The right stage gets mapped after.</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-parchment/72">
      You do not need to guess perfectly before you apply. Apply once, describe your current stage honestly, and the fit review can map
      you to the right point in the ladder without turning this into a hypey sales funnel.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-parchment/66">
      Founding models receive real structured work, not placeholder advice, and they keep the outputs created for them: naming direction,
      handle and platform-fit recommendations, room and tip-menu recommendations, progressive goal structure, front-door setup logic, and
      event ideas where relevant.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href={withBase('/apply/')}>Apply for Signup Guidance</a>
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="mailto:concierge@naughtycamspot.com?subject=NCS%20Offer%20Ladder">Ask a question</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
